<h1>AI Chat System — User Guide</h1>
<p>This guide explains how the AI chat widget reads your prompt, picks the right agent and model, and decides what to do — for helpdesk staff and developers.</p>

<hr>

<div class="ai-doc-section" id="how-it-works">
<h2>How It Works — The Full Flow</h2>

<p>Every time you type a message in the chat widget, the system follows these steps:</p>

<div class="flow-box">
    <div class="flow-step">
        <div class="step-num">1</div>
        <div><strong>Page Detection</strong> — The widget reads the current URL and page title to understand where you are (e.g., on an ENCY herb page, a BMaster hive page, a todo task, etc.).</div>
    </div>
    <div class="flow-step">
        <div class="step-num">2</div>
        <div><strong>Agent Selection</strong> — Based on the URL, the system picks the best specialist agent (ENCY, BMaster, Accounting, HelpDesk, etc.). The agent defines what the AI knows and can do on this page.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="flow-step">
        <div class="step-num">3</div>
        <div><strong>Prompt Classification</strong> — Your message is classified by type: navigation command, form-fill request, or open question. Simple or fast requests are handled locally (no AI needed); complex questions go to the AI model.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="flow-step">
        <div class="step-num">4</div>
        <div><strong>Model Selection</strong> — If the AI is needed, the system picks the appropriate model based on complexity: a small fast model for simple questions, a larger model for complex research or multi-step tasks. Cloud models (Grok) are used for hard questions when Ollama is unavailable.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="flow-step">
        <div class="step-num">5</div>
        <div><strong>Context Injection</strong> — The server automatically adds live data (todo details, ENCY plant records, hive data, page content) to the AI's context. You do NOT need to paste data — it's already there.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="flow-step">
        <div class="step-num">6</div>
        <div><strong>Response &amp; Action</strong> — The AI responds with text, a navigation link, or a pre-filled form action. The widget then executes the action (navigating the page, filling form fields, etc.).</div>
    </div>
</div>
</div>

<hr>

<div class="ai-doc-section" id="prompt-types">
<h2>Prompt Types — What You Can Ask</h2>

<h3>1. Open Questions <span class="tag tag-ai">AI responds</span></h3>
<p>Any question about the current page, a record, or a topic. The AI reads the live data already injected and answers.</p>
<div class="prompt-example"><strong>Examples:</strong><br>
    "What are the medicinal uses of Yarrow?"<br>
    "Is this hive inspection normal for this time of year?"<br>
    "What does naturopathic_medicine mean in the pharmacological_effects field?"<br>
    "How do I interpret this todo description?"
</div>
<p><strong>What happens:</strong> The message goes to the AI model. The AI has the current page's content (herb record, hive data, todo text) already loaded. It answers using that live data.</p>

<h3>2. Navigation Commands <span class="tag tag-fast">Instant — no AI needed</span></h3>
<p>Asking the widget to open a section or page. On ENCY pages, section keywords trigger instant navigation without an AI round-trip.</p>
<div class="prompt-example"><strong>Examples:</strong><br>
    "Open herbs list"<br>
    "Show me the glossary"<br>
    "Browse diseases"<br>
    "Go to the constituents list"<br>
    "Open the formulas section"
</div>
<p><strong>What happens:</strong> The widget detects the navigation intent and section keyword (herbs, glossary, diseases, etc.) and immediately navigates the current browser window to the correct page. The page changes — the chat widget reappears on the new page, ready to continue.</p>

<p><strong>ENCY section keywords that trigger instant navigation:</strong></p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Herbs / Plants / Botanical</strong> → <code>/ENCY/herbs</code></li>
    <li><strong>Constituents</strong> → <code>/ENCY/Constituent</code></li>
    <li><strong>Glossary</strong> → <code>/ENCY/glossary</code></li>
    <li><strong>Diseases</strong> → <code>/ENCY/diseases</code></li>
    <li><strong>Symptoms</strong> → <code>/ENCY/symptoms</code></li>
    <li><strong>Formula / Recipe</strong> → <code>/ENCY/formula</code></li>
    <li><strong>Insects</strong> → <code>/ENCY/insects</code></li>
    <li><strong>Animals</strong> → <code>/ENCY/animals</code></li>
    <li><strong>Pollinators / Bee Pasture / Forage</strong> → <code>/ENCY/BeePastureView</code></li>
</ul>

<h3>3. Form Fill Requests <span class="tag tag-ai">AI + action</span></h3>
<p>Asking the AI to fill in a form on the current page, or to navigate to a form and pre-populate it.</p>
<div class="prompt-example"><strong>Examples:</strong><br>
    "Please fill in this form with information about Yarrow"<br>
    "Fill the herb details using what you know about Echinacea"<br>
    "Add the constituent naturopathic_medicine using the details from todo #616"<br>
    "Open the invoice form and fill it with this bill: [paste bill text]"
</div>
<p><strong>What happens:</strong> The AI reads the form fields visible on the page (or navigates to the target form page), then fills in each field using available data — herb records, todo text, or information you provide. A confirmation step shows the proposed values before they are applied.</p>

<h3>4. Action Requests <span class="tag tag-ai">AI + action</span></h3>
<p>Asking the AI to take a specific action, like adding a missing record or fixing an unresolved term.</p>
<div class="prompt-example"><strong>Examples:</strong><br>
    "Add the constituent naturopathic_medicine as a new glossary entry"<br>
    "Fix the unresolved term in constituent #17"<br>
    "Open the add constituent form for this term"
</div>
<p><strong>What happens:</strong> The AI reads the todo/task context already injected, identifies the term name, and opens the correct add/edit form pre-filled with the known data.</p>
</div>

<hr>

<div class="ai-doc-section" id="agents">
<h2>Agents — Specialists for Each Area</h2>
<p>Each agent has a pre-built system prompt tailored to a specific part of the application. The agent is automatically selected based on the current page URL.</p>

<table class="role-table">
    <tr>
        <th>Agent</th>
        <th>Activated On</th>
        <th>What It Knows</th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>🌿 <strong>ENCY</strong></td>
        <td>Any <code>/ENCY/</code> page</td>
        <td>Herbs, plants, constituents, diseases, symptoms, formulas, glossary, therapeutic actions, drug interactions. Has live herb and constituent data injected automatically.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>🐝 <strong>BMaster</strong></td>
        <td><code>/BMaster/</code>, <code>/Apiary/</code></td>
        <td>Beekeeping, hive management, inspections, honey production, varroa mite control, forage plants, bee pasture planning.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>💰 <strong>Accounting</strong></td>
        <td><code>/Inventory/</code>, <code>/accounting/</code></td>
        <td>Invoices, bills, suppliers, purchase orders. Can parse a pasted bill and pre-fill the invoice entry form.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>🎫 <strong>HelpDesk</strong></td>
        <td><code>/HelpDesk/</code>, <code>/support/</code></td>
        <td>Technical support, troubleshooting, creating tickets, escalation.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>📋 <strong>Planning</strong></td>
        <td><code>/planning/</code>, <code>/project/</code></td>
        <td>Projects, sub-projects, plans, todos, sprint status, blocking tasks. Live project and todo data injected automatically.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>📚 <strong>Documentation</strong></td>
        <td><code>/Documentation/</code>, <code>/docs/</code>, <code>/help/</code></td>
        <td>System documentation, user guides, how-to help.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>💻 <strong>Coding</strong> (admin only)</td>
        <td><code>/ai/</code>, <code>/admin/</code></td>
        <td>Perl/Catalyst backend, DBIx::Class, TT2 templates, JavaScript. Can read files, propose fixes.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>✏️ <strong>Template Editor</strong> (admin only)</td>
        <td>Any page (manual selection)</td>
        <td>Reviews and rewrites TT2 template files for the current page.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>🤖 <strong>General</strong></td>
        <td>All other pages</td>
        <td>General-purpose assistant — answers questions using the current page content.</td>
    </tr>
</table>

<h3>How Agent Selection Works</h3>
<div class="flow-box">
    <ol>
        <li>The widget reads <code>window.location.pathname</code> (the current URL path).</li>
        <li>It compares the path against each agent's <code>url_patterns</code> list (from <code>/static/config/agents.json</code>).</li>
        <li>The first matching pattern wins. More specific patterns win over shorter ones.</li>
        <li>If no pattern matches, the <strong>General</strong> agent is used.</li>
        <li>In popup or task-context mode, the agent is selected from the <em>originating page</em> path — not the popup URL.</li>
    </ol>
</div>

<p>The active agent is shown in the chat header. You can also manually switch agents using the agent selector if available.</p>
</div>

<hr>

<div class="ai-doc-section" id="models">
<h2>Model Selection — How the AI Picks the Right Engine</h2>

<h3>Automatic Tier Classification</h3>
<p>Every prompt is automatically classified into a complexity tier. The tier determines which AI provider and model size is used:</p>

<table class="role-table">
    <tr>
        <th>Tier</th>
        <th>Prompt Type</th>
        <th>Provider</th>
        <th>Speed</th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><strong>Nav</strong></td>
        <td>Navigation command (open page, go to section)</td>
        <td>None — instant local fast path</td>
        <td>Instant</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><strong>Simple</strong></td>
        <td>Short factual question (&lt;10 words)</td>
        <td>Ollama — small model (3–8B)</td>
        <td>Fast (5–30 s)</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><strong>Medium</strong></td>
        <td>Moderate question with context</td>
        <td>Ollama — medium model (8–14B)</td>
        <td>Standard (30–120 s)</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><strong>Complex</strong></td>
        <td>Multi-step reasoning, code, research</td>
        <td>Ollama large or Grok (cloud)</td>
        <td>Advanced (60 s – 10 min)</td>
    </tr>
</table>

<h3>Ollama vs Grok</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Ollama</strong> — Runs locally on your own server. Private, no data leaves your network. Slower on CPU hardware; much faster if GPU is available. Has a 10-minute timeout for cold starts.</li>
    <li><strong>Grok (xAI)</strong> — Cloud model. Fast response (seconds), supports large context windows and web search. Used automatically when Ollama is overloaded, or you can switch manually using the provider dropdown.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Manual Override</h3>
<p>You can override the automatic selection at any time using the provider/model dropdown in the chat header. Select <em>Grok</em> for fast cloud responses, or pick a specific Ollama model if you need a particular capability.</p>

<h3>Timeout and Retry</h3>
<p>If Ollama takes too long (over 11 minutes), the widget shows a <strong>Retry Ollama</strong> button and a <strong>Switch to Grok</strong> button. Clicking "Switch to Grok" immediately resends your question to the cloud model. A <strong>✕ Cancel</strong> button is also available during any request to abort it immediately.</p>
</div>

<hr>

