<div class="ai-doc-section" id="examples">
<h2>Examples — Common Use Cases</h2>

<h3>Answering a Question About a Record</h3>
<div class="prompt-example">"What is naturopathic medicine and why is it in the pharmacological effects field?"</div>
<p><strong>What happens:</strong> The ENCY agent is active (you're on an ENCY page). The server has already injected the constituent record into the AI's context. The AI reads it and answers directly — no need to copy/paste anything.</p>

<h3>Opening a Section of ENCY</h3>
<div class="prompt-example">"Open herbs list" &nbsp;or&nbsp; "Show me the glossary"</div>
<p><strong>What happens:</strong> The widget instantly detects "herbs" or "glossary" as an ENCY section keyword and navigates the browser window to <code>/ENCY/herbs</code> or <code>/ENCY/glossary</code> — no AI call, no wait.</p>

<h3>Filling In a Form About a Herb</h3>
<div class="prompt-example">"Please fill in this form with information about Yarrow"</div>
<p><strong>What happens:</strong> The AI reads the form fields on the current page, then uses its knowledge of Yarrow (common name, botanical name, medicinal uses, constituents) to suggest values for each field. The user reviews the suggestions and confirms before they are applied.</p>

<h3>Adding a Missing Constituent</h3>
<div class="prompt-example">"Add the constituent naturopathic_medicine from todo #616"</div>
<p><strong>What happens:</strong> The ENCY agent reads the injected todo data, finds the term name and context, then opens the <em>Add Constituent</em> form (<code>/ENCY/Constituent/add</code>) with the name pre-filled. The user can then complete and save the record.</p>

<h3>Filing an Invoice</h3>
<div class="prompt-example">[Paste the text of a bill or invoice] then: "Enter this invoice"</div>
<p><strong>What happens:</strong> The Accounting agent parses the pasted bill (supplier name, invoice number, date, total amount), then opens the invoice entry form (<code>/Inventory/invoice/new</code>) pre-filled with the extracted values. The user verifies and saves.</p>

<h3>Asking for Support</h3>
<div class="prompt-example">"The hive inspection report is not saving — what should I check?"</div>
<p><strong>What happens:</strong> On a BMaster page, the BMaster agent responds with troubleshooting steps. On a HelpDesk page, the HelpDesk agent responds and may offer to create a support ticket. If the issue is unclear, the agent asks a clarifying question.</p>
</div>

<hr>

<div class="ai-doc-section">
<h2>Tips for Better Results</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Be on the right page</strong> — The AI automatically reads the current page's data. If you're asking about herb #42, open that herb's page first.</li>
    <li><strong>Use ENCY section keywords</strong> for instant navigation: "herbs", "glossary", "diseases", "symptoms", "formula", "constituents".</li>
    <li><strong>For form fill</strong> — make sure you're on the form page before asking the AI to fill it, or say "open the add form for…" to navigate and fill in one step.</li>
    <li><strong>If Ollama is slow</strong> — use the <em>Switch to Grok</em> button that appears on timeout, or pre-select Grok from the provider dropdown for immediate responses.</li>
    <li><strong>Voice input</strong> — Click the microphone button to speak your prompt. The system transcribes it and sends it as text. Useful when your hands are occupied.</li>
    <li><strong>Conversation history</strong> — The AI remembers the last few exchanges in your session. You can refer back ("the one we just discussed") and it understands.</li>
    <li><strong>The AI does not guess URLs</strong> — It only navigates to pages it knows about from the system prompt. If you ask to open an unknown page, it will ask you to clarify.</li>
</ul>
</div>
